ination and=\r\n do so. But never try to force it on an unwilling individual. Whenever forc=\r\ne is applied, it invariable leads to a unpredictable and at times unpleasan=\r\nt reaction at some later\n date. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nOne of the people whom I consider=\r\n as one of my gurus, had told me once, &quot;Duniya banane wala duniya chalana b=\r\nhi janta hai&quot; (One who made the world also knows how to run the world). Now=\r\n I believe that statement is bang on. Feel no pressure. Everything is in sa=\r\nfe hands!&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;&lt; 5. Why =C3=82 did Gautam Buddha left his wife a=\r\nnd his child and even then achieved the status of God?&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIn =\r\nmy view, we use the term God too loosely. There are Mahatmas, great Mahatma=\r\ns, fantastic spiritual beings, and then there is God. Buddha was a fantasti=\r\nc and super-duper spiritual being.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow coming to your question, th=\r\nere is no fixed rule of how and what can lead a man to liberation or higher=\r\n states of spirituality. Frankly, there is no path which *guarantees* liber=\r\nation. All paths have the potential, but realization is an individual&#39;s jou=\r\nrney, and each such journey will not be a mirror of anyone else&#39;s journey. =\r\nBroadly there may be similarities, but nuances will differ. For some it is =\r\nnecessary to leave their wife and children to be spiritual, for others they=\r\n may not need to do so. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nInfact, the aim of sadhana is to prepare =\r\nyourself. If and when you experience and realize God, it is going be God&#39;s =\r\nsweet will. Sadhana does not guarantee realization, but without sadhana it =\r\nis nearly impossibly, for you are simply not prepared enough to experience.=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;&lt;3. I was reading =C3=82 a newspaper that people after ha=\r\nving darshan of Mata Vaishno Devi, Kedarnaath, etc =C3=82 , while returning=\r\n, met with accident and died. Why does this happen? People have just come f=\r\nrom a such a wonderful darshan then why tragedy strikes them.&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\nThe idea of trying to force a cause effect relation to everything is a=\r\nn inherent tendency of the mind. It is not necessarily how things are. Neit=\r\nher is it useful.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIf a man wants to only experience God, then ever=\r\ny life-experience, apparently good or apparently bad, is only going to take=\r\n your forward towards the goal if you keep your aim fixed. No wonder Lord K=\r\nrishna stresses so much on detachment and equanimity in his advice to Arjun=\r\na, rather than trying to find out cause-effect relationships of the apparen=\r\ntly good or the apparently bad kinds. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSufferings are a great way =\r\nof focusing on God. Really. Slowly but surely you realize that the world wi=\r\nll run in its own pattern and you cannot do much about it, except control w=\r\nhat is in your power to control, that is your internal state. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nKri=\r\nshna gives this advice to Arjuna in the Second Chapter: &quot;Dukhesva Anudhvign=\r\na-manah Sukhesu-Vigatasprhah Vita-Raga-Bhaya-Krodhah Sthita-Dhira Munir Uch=\r\nyate&quot; Gita 2:56 [Miseries do not agitate the mind, in sukha (fleeting happi=\r\nness) there is no elation, such a one who is free from attachment, fear and=\r\n anger, is a sage of steady mind.]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nTough? Sure. But no harm in mak=\r\ning an effort. This is something to be tried on a regular basis, day in and=\r\n day out.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;&lt;2. Persons who do nothing =C3=82 in the field of=\r\n spirituality can also meet God, higher saints. How is it possible?&gt;&gt;=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nDepends on what we understand by the term spirituality. Many have=\r\n this notion that spirituality only means sitting and doing tough penances =\r\nETC. There is more to spirituality than that. Essentially, it is a transfor=\r\nmation of mind, emotions and body (this bit is nearly impossible) into anot=\r\nher state. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSadhana is needed to prepare the ground - mind/emotion=\r\ns/body. But *meeting God* (as you put it) depends on what you mean by God, =\r\nand on God&#39;s sweet will. Sometimes, living your daily life with an internal=\r\n sense of surrender to a Supreme, trying to inculcate equanimity in testing=\r\n circumstances, trying to stop the mind from automatically reacting to prov=\r\nocations, seeing other people&#39;s point of views and thus becoming more objec=\r\ntive, trying to be compassionate (but not self-pity or pity in any form, fo=\r\nr pity is a degenerative emotion, while compassion is uplifting) ETC are al=\r\nl sadhanas which can be done by anybody. One need not read complex scriptur=\r\nes, or believe in religion to be able to do these. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;&lt;1. Aft=\r\ner effect of Homam can be negative also. Is it true?&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nAfter=\r\n effect of any sadhana can be negative (or positive), if your aim is anythi=\r\nng materialistic. If your aim is purely spiritual transformation, both so c=\r\nalled negative and so called positive will help you. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;&lt;Fulf=\r\nilling the duties of husband is a blockage in the spiritual path.&gt;&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nDharma is never a blockage. When the time is ripe, the Lord sets th=\r\ne path. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWhen Lord Krishna send Uddhava - who was a gyani of the f=\r\nirst order - to the Gopis, he was amazed to see that the Gopis would spend =\r\nthe whole day doing whatever they must do, but they would perform every act=\r\nion, even the most mundane like clearing the garbage, with a small prayer i=\r\nn their lips, &quot;Sri KrishNaaya Samarpayami..&quot;. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nPatience and surren=\r\nder to God can be inculcated, progressively, in any life situation. Infact,=\r\n it is the ONLY thing that you can work on. Rest, the world around apart fr=\r\nom you, will follow its own rhythm which has been decided by actions perfor=\r\nmed in the past which one may or maynot be aware of. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nEvery blocka=\r\nge is an opportunity to increase the sense of surrender to something Higher=\r\n, and that in turn acts as a powerful internal catalyst for change.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\nCaveat: These answers are based on my current perspective of things. They=\r\n may not be sacrosanct. In future, I myself may or may-not agree to these a=\r\nnswers -:)&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n-Regards&lt;br&gt;\n Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;\n--- In &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; y=\r\nmailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;=\r\nmailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;, ga=\r\nurav tripathi &lt;gaurav_alld@...&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Dear All Lea=\r\nrned members,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp; =C3=82&nbsp;Following are my questions:=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 1. After effect of Homam can be negative also. Is it true?&lt;br&gt;\n&g=\r\nt; 2. Persons who do nothing =C3=82&nbsp;in the field of spirituality can a=\r\nlso meet God, higher saints. How is it possible?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 3. I was reading =\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;a newspaper that people after having darshan of Mata Vaishno De=\r\nvi, Kedarnaath, etc =C3=82&nbsp;, while returning, met with accident and di=\r\ned. Why does this happen? People have just come from a such a wonderful dar=\r\nshan then why tragedy strikes them.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 4. People who are married and =\r\nhave the wife and kid as responsibilities. Fulfilling the duties of husband=\r\n is a blockage in the spiritual path. You know =C3=82&nbsp;what i mean.=C3=\r\n=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 5. Why =C3=82&nbsp;did Gautam Buddha left his wife and h=\r\nis child and even then achieved the status of God?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 6. A common per=\r\nson gives =C3=82&nbsp;a damn to the concept